NSD – Documentation & Website

Overview

This document describes the documentation structure and website for the NSD (Network Suspicious Detection) project.

The documentation website provides technical documentation, system architecture information, API references, deployment guides, and project information for developers, operators, and stakeholders.

⸻

Documentation Goals

The documentation site should:
	•	Explain what NSD is
	•	Describe system architecture
	•	Provide developer documentation
	•	Provide API documentation
	•	Provide deployment instructions
	•	Provide security and privacy policies
	•	Provide project roadmap and updates
	•	Help onboard new developers and contributors

